posts.description: Last night I finally got out for my first astro shoot of the season. Was great to see the galactic core once again after the weeks of cloudy nights that we've had recently and not being able to head out when the conditions were right. Really looking forward to capturing more images like this in the coming months! üåå

Finishing off the Outback series tonight with one of my favourite photos from the trip and it's an image of the Living Desert and Sculptures in Broken Hill, couldn't resist from getting the sun star through one of the sculptures. I hope you've enjoyed my mini Outback NSW series over the last couple of weeks. I had an amazing time exploring the Outback and shooting something a little bit different for a change. If you want to see a few more shots and a video head over to my website where I just published a new blog post about the trip (link in bio). Lastly, be sure to tag your NSW holidays with #ilovensw. #newsouthwales @visitnsw

A classic Australian outback scene at sunset, it doesn't really get much more classic than this! I had an awesome time shooting this spot, it felt like I was in the middle of a desert. Such a cool experience! Don't forget to tag your NSW holidays with #ilovensw. #newsouthwales @visitnsw

First light and endless plains. This is what Mundi Mundi Plains looks like from up above. Pretty crazy that you can see more than 150km from the top of the hill. The view from the ground is just as impressive as it is from the air! Share what you love about holidays in NSW using #ilovensw. #newsouthwales @visitnsw

Full moon rising over the vast desert vistas of Broken Hill. After photographing the sculptures at sunset I stuck around for a little bit to watch the moon rise from the top of the Living Desert. Early morning light hitting the Pinnacles in Broken Hill. Loved watching the sunrise from up above in the outback and also being able to capture a different perspective of the vast landscapes. The Living Desert and Sculptures at dusk. This was one of my favourite spots that I visited while in Outback NSW. It's a great place to watch the sunset from just a few minutes drive out of Broken Hill, deffinetly worth a visit to see the 12 sculptures and the amazing views of the outback. The dead trees around the shores of Lake Menindee catching the last rays of sun as it sets in Outback NSW. The lake is full of dead trees and it's an incredible sight to see, even more so at sunset when all the trees start glowing red.
